69066d4fc007ca8c273814a7%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221106%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EBruce%20Adams%20had%20a%20%26quot%3Bwidow-maker%26quot%3B%20heart%20attack%20during%20a%20meeting.%20Returning%20to%20work%20was%20harder%20than%20he%20had%20expected.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Cooperative%20Credit%20Union%20Association%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EBruce%20Adams%20had%20a%20heart%20attack%20during%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcutting-work-meetings-can-make-you-happier-and-more-productive-2024-7%5C%22%20data-autoaffiliated%3D%5C%22false%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ework%20meeting%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%202024.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EAdams%2C%20who%20is%20CEO%20of%20the%20Credit%20Union%20League%20of%20Connecticut%2C%20spent%20six%20months%20recovering.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHis%20team%20thrived%20in%20his%20absence%2C%20which%20made%20Adams%20question%20whether%20he%20was%20still%20needed.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20as-told-to%20essay%20is%20based%20on%20a%20conversation%20with%20Bruce%20Adams%2C%2052%2C%20who%20lives%20in%20West%20Hartford%2C%20Connecticut.%20He%20is%20the%20CEO%20of%20the%20Credit%20Union%20League%20of%20Connecticut%2C%20a%20trade%20association.%20In%20October%202024%2C%20Adams%20had%20a%20heart%20attack%20and%20spent%20six%20months%20away%20from%20work%20as%20he%20recovered.%20This%20story%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20a%20particularly%20stressful%20morning.%20I%20was%20at%20my%20desk%20in%20my%20home%20office%2C%20meeting%20with%20my%20team%20to%20finalize%20the%20details%20for%20our%20upcoming%20trade%20show.%20I%20stood%20up%20to%20get%20a%20bottle%20of%20water%2C%20and%20I%20didn't%20make%20it%2010%20feet%20before%20I%20started%20hyperventilating.%20I%20had%20to%20lie%20down%20on%20the%20floor.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20texted%20my%20girlfriend%20and%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BSomething's%20happening%20to%20me.%20Cold%20sweats.%20Pain%20in%20my%20chest%2C%20but%20no%20arm%20pain.%20Doesn't%20feel%20like%20a%20heavy%20weight.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20called%209-1-1.%20I%20texted%20my%20COO%20and%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BI'm%20not%20coming%20back%20to%20the%20meeting.%20Something%20is%20wrong.%26quot%3B%20I%20texted%20my%20PR%20guy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20hospital%2C%20they%20determined%20that%20I%20was%20having%20what's%20sometimes%20called%20a%20%26quot%3Bwidow-maker%26quot%3B%20heart%20attack.%20I%20had%20five%20blockages%2C%20so%20they%20had%20to%20do%20emergency%20bypass%20graft%20surgery.%20They%20sent%20me%20right%20over%20to%20the%20OR%2C%20and%20nine%20hours%20later%2C%20I%20was%20in%20the%20ICU.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBefore%20going%20into%20surgery%2C%20I%20was%20able%20to%20talk%20to%20my%20girlfriend%20and%20some%20people%20who%20had%20come%20to%20visit.%20That%20was%20when%20I%20finally%20got%20emotional.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBefore%20that%2C%20it%20was%20all%20work%20%E2%80%94%20still%20trying%20to%20get%20my%20PR%20guy%20to%20be%20ready%20to%20do%20a%20statement.%20It%20was%20a%20little%20irrational%20because%20there's%20a%20smidge%20of%2C%20perhaps%2C%20too%20much%20self-importance.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20run%20a%20membership%20organization%2C%20and%20there%20were%20going%20to%20be%20hundreds%20of%20people%20at%20this%20trade%20show%20where%20I'd%20be%20conspicuously%20absent.%20Yet%2C%20I'm%20also%20not%20that%20important.%20The%20show%20is%20going%20to%20happen%20without%20me.%20But%20when%20you're%20having%20that%20breakout%20moment%2C%20everything%20becomes%20super%20important.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%229d427490-88df-4f7c-8ba1-dbaa3388e38f%5C%22%3EMy%20recovery%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20view%20my%20time%20off%20from%20work%20as%20two%20chunks.%20The%20first%20three%20months%20were%20mostly%20physical%2C%20and%20the%20second%20few%20months%20were%20mostly%20mental%20and%20emotional.%20I'm%20blessed%20to%20have%20been%20given%20the%20time%20to%20recover.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20course%20of%20finishing%20the%20first%20three%20months%2C%20I%20realized%20that%20maybe%20there%20are%20questions%20I%20ought%20to%20think%20about%2C%20like%2C%20%26quot%3BWhy%20did%20I%20walk%20away%20from%20the%20plane%20crash%2C%20metaphorically%20speaking%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20found%20a%20therapist%20who%20specializes%20in%20near-death%20experiences%20and%20medical%20crises.%20I%20had%20a%20therapist%20before.%20I'm%20a%20big%20fan%20of%20getting%20a%20regular%20mental%20tune-up%2C%20like%20an%20oil%20change%20for%20your%20car.%20She%20helped%20me%20ask%20hard%20questions%20and%20pointed%20me%20toward%20living%20a%20life%20that%20has%20time%20for%20parenting%2C%20work%2C%20rest%2C%20and%20play.%20I've%20been%20reminded%20in%20the%20worst%20possible%20way%20that%20we%20only%20have%20one%20shot%20at%20this.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2260ee3777-d7d2-4a12-b7df-2e840d4f8f79%5C%22%3EGoing%20back%20to%20work%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20had%20switched%20offices%20between%20the%20time%20I%20left%20and%20came%20back.%20I%20didn't%20have%20a%20badge%20to%20get%20into%20the%20building%20or%20know%20where%20the%20bathroom%20was.%20I%20felt%20like%20the%20new%20guy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20scared.%20I%20didn't%20know%20that%20I%20could%20get%20my%20engine%20turning%20at%20the%20same%20RPMs%20as%20it%20was%20before.%20I%20didn't%20know%20if%20I%20would%20be%20a%20drag%20on%20the%20people%20who%20had%20figured%20out%20how%20to%20move%20forward%20without%20me.%20I%20thought%2C%20as%20the%20CEO%2C%20I've%20got%20the%20biggest%20item%20on%20the%20budget's%20wage%20line.%20Will%20people%20think%20I'm%20not%20worth%20it%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20was%20a%20few%20weeks%20of%20manageable%2C%20but%20actual%2C%20fear.%20Then%20it%20struck%20me%20that%20the%20whole%20reason%20I%20had%20that%20fear%20was%20because%20I%20had%20set%20that%20team%20in%20place%20%E2%80%94%20and%20they%20were%20able%20to%20do%20it%20without%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20systems%20we%20had%20in%20place%2C%20and%20the%20people%20operating%20those%20systems%2C%20were%20not%20only%20able%20to%20respond%20in%20that%20immediate%20moment%20of%20our%20trade%20show%20%E2%80%94%20not%20knowing%20whether%20I'd%20live%20or%20die%20%E2%80%94%20but%20also%20for%20the%20next%20six%20months.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20had%20to%20honor%20what%20they%20did%20and%20accept%20that%20they%20could%20do%20it%20without%20me.%20At%20the%20same%20time%2C%20I%20had%20to%20accept%20that%20I%20still%20had%20something%20to%20offer.%20Those%20two%20things%20are%20hard%20to%20align%2C%20but%20are%20so%20important.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20first%20board%20meeting%20back%20was%20weird%20because%20normally%2C%20as%20the%20CEO%2C%20you're%20presenting%20the%20financials%20and%20talking%20strategy.%20But%20what%20could%20I%20talk%20about%3F%20I%20had%20been%20gone%20for%20six%20months.%20Our%20COO%2C%20who%20had%20been%20the%20acting%20CEO%2C%20was%20sitting%20next%20to%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20board%20had%20lived%20its%20own%20sort%20of%20trauma%2C%20and%20the%20COO%20had%2C%20too.%20We%20had%20stayed%20in%20touch%2C%20so%20I%20knew%20what%20was%20happening%20at%20work%2C%20and%20I%20was%20able%20to%20help%20make%20some%20decisions.%20But%20I%20had%20said%20to%20her%2C%20%26quot%3BI'm%20helping%20you%20as%20your%20friend%2C%20and%20you%20don't%20want%20me%20to%20have%20surprises%20when%20I%20come%20back.%20But%20whatever%20decisions%20you%20make%2C%20I'm%20going%20to%20back%20you%20up.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20I%20was%20back%2C%20during%20conversations%20with%20our%20members%2C%20I%20heard%2C%20%26quot%3BJeez%2C%20your%20team%20did%20so%20great%20while%20you%20were%20gone.%26quot%3B%20And%20I%20thought%2C%20%26quot%3BI%20built%20a%20team%20that%20was%20able%20to%20withstand%20such%20a%20big%20shock.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20was%20very%2C%20very%20gratifying.%20I've%20always%20been%20sort%20of%20a%20lead-from-behind%20guy%2C%20but%20I%20am%20even%20more%20so%20now.%20The%