ing%20cash%20flow%20immediately.%20Plus%2C%20he%20found%20a%20roommate%20for%20his%20unit.%20The%20rent%20from%20his%20two%20tenants%20covered%20the%20majority%20of%20his%20monthly%20mortgage%20payment%2C%20allowing%20him%20to%20save%20more%20money%20for%20his%20next%20property.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENewton%2C%20who%20has%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstate-trooper-using-real-estate-investing-financial-independence-retire-early-2022-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eexpanded%20to%20over%2010%20units%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20considers%20this%20strategy%2C%20known%20as%20%26quot%3Bhouse%20hacking%2C%26quot%3B%20one%20of%20%26quot%3Bthe%20safest%20ways%20that%20you%20can%20start%20investing%20in%20real%20estate.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20renting%20a%20portion%20of%20your%20primary%20residence%2C%20you%20can%20offset%20or%20even%20completely%20eliminate%20your%20mortgage.%20It's%20a%20relatively%20low-risk%20way%20to%20see%20if%20you%20enjoy%20being%20a%20landlord%20and%20managing%20tenants.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20worth%20noting%20that%20not%20all%20markets%20have%20an%20abundance%20of%20multifamily%20properties.%20The%20New%20England%20market%20happens%20to%20have%20a%20large%20inventory%20of%20these%20properties%2C%20explained%20Bull%3A%20%26quot%3BThese%20buildings%20were%20created%20in%20the%20late%201800s%20and%20early%201900s%20as%20a%20way%20to%20economically%20house%20people%20in%20areas%20close%20to%20or%20around%20cities%20like%20Boston.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20there%20aren't%20multifamily%20properties%20in%20your%20area%2C%20you%20can%20still%20house%20hack%20a%20single-family%20home%20by%20adding%20an%20ADU%20or%20converting%20an%20unfinished%20basement%20into%20a%20rentable%20space%20%E2%80%94%20or%2C%20like%20Newton%2C%20finding%20a%20roommate.%20The%20name%20of%20the%20game%20is%20getting%20creative%20with%20your%20space%20so%20that%2C%20ultimately%2C%20other%20people%20are%20paying%20down%20your%20mortgage.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cd