2C%20and%20then%20even%20earlier%20as%20the%20trial%20went%20on.%20In%20the%20early%20morning%20hours%2C%20the%20ramp%20outside%20the%20courthouse%20would%20be%20packed%20with%20dozens%20of%20people%20huddled%20in%20sleeping%20bags%20or%20portable%20chairs.%20At%20night%2C%20temperatures%20would%20drop%20to%20the%2030s.%20Friends%20brought%20us%20lawn%20chairs%2C%20electric%20blankets%2C%20and%20disposable%20hand%20warmers%2C%20and%20we%20bundled%20in%20layers%20and%20blankets.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20case%20attracted%20a%20lot%20of%20unstable%20people%2C%20so%20sometimes%20we%20feared%20confrontations%20or%20fights%20breaking%20out%20in%20the%20line.%20But%20for%20the%20most%20part%2C%20those%20waiting%20to%20get%20into%20court%20got%20along%20well.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20least%20one%20of%20us%20managed%20to%20get%20into%20the%20trial%20every%20day.%20We%20gave%20up%20eating%20and%20drinking%20in%20the%20mornings%2C%20as%20heading%20to%20the%20restroom%20during%20the%20day%20would%20result%20in%20a%20forfeited%20seat.%20Every%20night%2C%20we'd%20go%20home%20and%20immediately%20record%20a%20multi-hour%20podcast%20episode%20based%20on%20pages%20and%20pages%20of%20trial%20notes.%20We%20struggled%20with%20fatigue%2C%20dehydration%2C%20hunger%2C%20and%20the%20cold%20for%20most%20of%20the%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEnduring%20the%20process%20together%20strengthened%20us.%20We%20learned%20to%20let%20a%20lot%20of%20minor%20annoyances%20go%20and%20made%20a%20pact%20to%20be%20as%20patient%2C%20calm%2C%20and%20compassionate%20with%20each%20other%20as%20we%20could%20be%20at%20all%20times.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKind%20listeners%20ended%20up%20volunteering%20to%20hold%20our%20spots%20in%20line%20as%20the%20weeks%20went%20on.%20We%20wouldn't%20have%20been%20able%20to%20report%20the%20story%20without%20them.%20As%20a%20result%20of%20our%20trial%20coverage%2C%20our%20podcast%20broke%20into%20the%20Top%20100%20list%20on%20Apple%20Podcasts%20for%20all%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-women-love-true-crime-so-much-2018-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Epodcasts%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20the%20first%20time%20ever.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%226d83a18a-c93b-48ee-9d8b-f2ae8639011a%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EWe%20had%20a%20limited%20time%20to%20complete%20the%20book%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOur%20book%2C%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faffiliate.insider.com%3Fh%3D935e0581a3653c4aa3cca4ee7fa75d6ad4c2130531af84e14a9eb662f31505a7%26postID%3D690681b1dcd4d48575d2de54%26postSlug%3Dcouple-true-crime-podcast-delphi-murder-book-2025-11%26site%3Dbi%26u%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fwww.amazon.com%252FShadow-Bridge-Murders-American-Heartland%252Fdp%252F1639369236%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EShadow%20of%20the%20Bridge%3A%20The%20Delphi%20Murders%20and%20the%20Dark%20Side%20of%20the%20American%20Heartland%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%26quot%3B%20includes%20exclusive%2C%20unprecedented%20access%20to%20the%20main%20players%20in%20the%20story%20%E2%80%94%20family%20members%2C%20prosecutors%2C%20detectives%2C%20and%20members%20of%20the%20Delphi%20community%20%E2%80%94%20and%20pieces%20together%20all%20the%20turns%20of%20the%20investigation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20the%20guilty%20verdict%20finally%20came%20in%2C%20it%20felt%20like%20we%20had%20spent%20a%20month%20on%20a%20dreary%2C%20depressing%20campout.%20Going%20inside%20and%20thawing%20out%20felt%20nice%2C%20and%20we%20had%20no%20doubt%20the%20jury%20got%20it%20right%2C%20but%20we%20couldn't%20relax.%20We%20had%20to%20scrap%20parts%20of%20our%20book%20draft%20and%20add%20complicated%20new%20details%20we'd%20learned%20in%20the%20trial%20while%20cutting%20extraneous%20minutiae%20so%20our%20readers%20wouldn't%20get%20lost.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20a%20month%2C%20we%20pulled%2015-hour%20workdays%2C%20working%20late%20into%20the%20night%20and%20on%20weekends.%20For%20a%20while%20we%20felt%20more%20like%20drudges%20in%20the%20same%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fquiet-quitting-bad-idea-instead-work-strategies-2022-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Emiserable%20workplace%3C%2Fa%3E%20than%20spouses%2C%20but%20we%20knew%20it%20would%20come%20to%20an%20end.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%225f718685-2a55-4891-8c69-2ec76a930803%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EIt%20was%20hard%2C%20but%20we're%20proud%20of%20what%20we%20did%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20book%20has%20been%20successful%20so%20far%2C%20and%20our%20publisher%20is%20happy.%20We%20are%20too.%20That%20said%2C%20no%20sensible%20person%20should%20get%20into%20book-writing%20to%20make%20big%20money%20%E2%80%94%20especially%20not%20crime%20nonfiction%20about%20a%20depressing%20double%20homicide.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22884%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20memorial%20to%20Libby%20and%20Abby%20sits%20along%20the%20trails%20of%20Delphi%2C%20Indiana.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6906cacdc007ca8c27381609%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221178%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20memorial%20to%20Libby%20and%20Abby%20sits%20along%20the%20trails%20of%20Delphi%2C%20Indiana.%3Cp%3EThe%20Murder%20Sheet%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20book%20was%20never%20a%20financial%20move%20for%20us.%20It%20helps%20build%20our%20profile%20and%20credibility%2C%20but%20more%20importantly%2C%20it%20shares%20the%20truth%20about%20a%20case%20with%20the%20public.%20It%20was%20an%20honor%20to%20get%20to%20tell%20the%20story%2C%20and%20witness%20firsthand%20the%20men%20and%20women%20%E2%80%94%20detectives%2C%20prosecutors%2C%20volunteers%2C%20and%20victims'%20relatives%20alike%20%E2%80%94%20who%20strived%20to%20get%20justice%20in%20the%20case.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOur%20hearts%20still%20are%20broken%20for%20those%20girls%20and%20their%20families.%20We%20gave%20a%20chunk%20of%20our%20advance%20to%20a%20charity%20that%20memorializes%20Libby%20and%20Abby%20with%20scholarship%20funds%20and%20a%20beautiful%20park.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20hardest%20part%20about%20covering%20Delphi%20has%20been%20questioning%20our%20faith%20in%20humanity.%20Not%20only%20did%20we%20cover%20a%20case%20where%20a%20man%20senselessly%20murdered%20two%20children%2C%20but%20we%20saw%20a%20lot%20of%20sordid%2C%20dishonorable%2C%20and%20downright%20bizarre%2C%20both%20in%20the%20courtroom%20and%20online%20from%20conspiracy%20theorists%20and%20content%20creators%20out%20to%20rake%20in%20views.%20Getting%20to%20observe%20and%20interview%20the%20men%20and%20women%20who%20truly%20cared%20about%20the%20girls%20gave%20us%20back%20some%20hope.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20want%20to%20keep%20covering%20cases%20meticulously%20and%20with%20empathy%20on%20the%20podcast%2C%20and%20to%20write%20more%20crime%20nonfiction%20books.%20Our%20ultimate%20goal%20is%20to%20fill%20up%20a%20whole%20shelf%20of%20our%20bookcase%20with%20works%20we%20wrote.%20This%20experience%20taught%20us%20what%20we%20are%20capable%20of%20and%20ultimately%20reminded%20us%20why%20we%20got%20into%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbest-true-crime-mysteries-podcasts-2018-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Etrue%20crime%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20to%20work%20closely%20together%20on%20a%20shared%20passion%20project%2C%20and%20to%20tell%20the%20stories%20of%20the%20human%20beings%20behind%20the%20headlines.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%C3%81ine%20Cain%20is%20a%20journalist%20who%20previously%20worked%20as%20a%20senior%20reporter%20for%20Business%20Insider.%20Kevin%20Greenlee%20is%20an%20attorney.%20Together%2C%20they%20are%20founders%20of%20The%20Murder%20Sheet%20and%20authors%20of%20new%20book.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcouple-true-crime-podcast-delphi-murder-book-2025-11%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1762078741000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F690699ac599d46a4ccc14d17%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A